ProspectiveStay - Reservation system for PPW

PREREQUISITES
  Node.js 18+ (recommend v20)
  PostgreSQL 14+

LOCAL DATABASE SETUP
  1. Create a PostgreSQL database:
       createdb prospective_stay
  2. Set the connection string in server/.env:
       DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/prospective_stay

SETUP
  cd server && npm install && npm run seed
  cd client && npm install

RUN (two terminals)
  Terminal 1:  cd server && npm run dev       (API on port 3001)
  Terminal 2:  cd client && npm run dev       (UI on port 5173)

  Open http://localhost:5173

LOGIN
  Enter any email address. Without SMTP configured, the 6-digit
  verification code is printed to the server console.

  Admin account: admin@ppw.com

EMAIL SETUP (optional)
  Add these to server/.env to send real emails:
    SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
    SMTP_PORT=587
    SMTP_SECURE=false
    SMTP_USER=you@gmail.com
    SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
    SMTP_FROM=you@gmail.com
    APP_URL=http://localhost:5173

  For Gmail, use an App Password (not your regular password):
    https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords

  Without SMTP vars, login codes are logged to the server console.

TESTS
  bash tests/run_tests.sh

DEPLOY TO RENDER.COM
  1. Create a new PostgreSQL database in Render dashboard.
  2. Create a new Web Service, connect your GitHub repo.
  3. Settings:
       Build Command:  cd server && npm install && cd ../client && npm install && npm run build
       Start Command:  cd server && node seed.js && node index.js
  4. Environment variables:
       DATABASE_URL    = (use Internal Database URL from your Render PostgreSQL instance)
       NODE_ENV        = production
       APP_URL         = https://your-app.onrender.com
       SMTP_HOST       = (your SMTP host)
       SMTP_PORT       = 587
       SMTP_USER       = (your email)
       SMTP_PASS       = (your email password or app password)
       SMTP_FROM       = (sender address)
